OL,3,CFamily of man killed then dismembered
OL,4,C'haunted' by his murder
OL,6,F"But we said from the start that we
OL,7,Fwouldn't give up and the victim and
OL,8,Ftheir family remained at the forefront
OL,9,Fof our minds and actions throughout.
OL,11,F"We knew from the beginning that we
OL,12,Fhad a family somewhere that would one
OL,13,Fday learn the most distressing news
OL,14,Fthat a family could ever hear, and
OL,15,Fultimately from that moment onwards
OL,16,Four duty was to recover and identify
OL,17,Fthe victim in a respectful and
OL,18,Fdignified manner and this was just as
OL,19,Fimportant as solving the case and
OL,20,Fcatching the killer.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOU
